         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Rotterdam 3 August 1863. ¶ Dr Meuller ¶ Botanical Gardens, ¶ Melbourne. ¶ Dear Sir,...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">63.08.03</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From the Board of the Zoological Society of Rotterdam</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M106, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Impressed stamp: ‘Rotterdamsche Diergaarde 1857’.</p>
               </note>Rotterdam 3 August 1863.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dr Meuller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Botanical Gardens,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Board of the Zoological Society of Rotterdam, named "Rotterdamsche Diergaarde" were much gratified, to learn that you have been so kind as to send them p.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">per.</p>
               </note> Capt ter Brugge, of the Dutch Bark<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Barque.</p>
               </note> "Vrede"</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>2 Cape Baron Geese Cereopsis Novae Hollandiae</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>2 Native Hens Porphirios …</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>They are Sorry to inform you that of these important birds only one of the Porphirios has arrived, the other three having died on the passage. — The Captain also was unlucky enough to lose the female of his two black Swans, given him by you, for his trouble in bringing over your valuable present.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Native Hen is already perfectly at home &amp; enjoys the best of health.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Board, gratiful for your kindness have Unanimously elected you Honorary Member of the Society, which mark of their approbation, they hope you will be pleased to accept.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>They beg to recommend the interests of the Gardens again to your powerful aid and trust the unfavorable issue of your first effort to enrich these collections will not deter you from sending, whenever you find an opportunity, any animals or birds you may deem fit for the Gardens.</p>
            <table n="Table1">
               <row>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.075in; padding-right: 0.075in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="valediction"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 0in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">P. H. Martin</p>
                  </cell>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.075in; padding-right: 0.075in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="valediction"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 0in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">A R Dunlop President</p>
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
                        xml:lang="en">[loco]<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                           <p rend="Footnote"
                              style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                              xml:lang="en">i.e. in place of; the President was J. van der Hoop Jacz, see the diploma that accompanied this letter (in this edition as 63-08-03a). <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Dunlop was a member of the committee (Kees Rookmaaker, personal communication, 26 November 2019).</p>
                        </note>
                     </p>
                  </cell>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.075in; padding-right: 0.075in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="valediction"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 0in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">Manager</p>
                  </cell>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.075in; padding-right: 0.075in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="valediction"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 0in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">N. J. Hoffmann Secretary</p>
                  </cell>
               </row>
            </table>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">P.S: Diploma enclosed.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See Rotterdamsche Diergaarde to M, 3 August 1863 (in this edition as 63-08-03a).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
